Shona Banda has said she will continue to fight for custody of her 11-year-old son . 
  Kansas authorities placed the boy into protective custody after he made comments during an anti-drug education program . 
  Banda uses cannabis oil to treat her Crohn's disease . 
  She could face possible charges for possession of marijuana and child endangerment . 
  The boy told school officials that his mother was a drug user . 
  The case of Banda, 37, has been forwarded to the district attorney . 
 